aty-perry-unconditionally-jesus|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|date=March 20, 2016|accessdate=April 6, 2016}}</ref> This version appears on the official soundtrack album.<ref name=AmazonCDSoundtrack>{{cite web|title=The Passion: New Orleans Soundtrack|url=https://www.amazon.com/Passion-New-Orleans-Soundtrack/dp/B01C5UN9JQ/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1459949565&sr=8-1&keywords=the+passion+soundtrack/|date=April 6, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Wikipedia books|Prism}}\n* [[List of number-one dance singles of 2014 (U.S.)]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Katy Perry}}\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Songs written by Katy Perry]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Dr. Luke]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Max Martin]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Max Martin]]\n[[Category:Katy Perry songs]]\n[[Category:2013 songs]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Cirkut (record producer)]]\n[[Category:2013 singles]]\n[[Category:2010s ballads]]\n[[Category:Pop ballads]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance Club Songs number-one singles]]\n", "name_user": "Kailash29792", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unconditionally"}
