 Shore Albions||1||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|21||S Houghton||Ponsonby United||1||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|21||J Cummings||Eden Ramblers||1||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|21||J O\u2019Sullivan||City Rovers||1||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|21||[[Ernie Asher]]||City Rovers||1||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|21||[[Ronald MacDonald (rugby league)|Ronald MacDonald]]||North Shore Albions||1||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|21||Roy Denize||City Rovers||1||-||-||-||-||-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.aucklandleague.co.nz/ Auckland Rugby League Official Site]\n\n[[Category:Auckland Rugby League seasons]]\n[[Category:Rugby league in Auckland]]\n[[Category:Rugby league governing bodies in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Rugby league]]\n", "text_old": "{{Cleanup|reason=drop caps as per [[MOS:HEADINGS]]|date=April 2020}}\nThe 1911 [[Auckland Rugby League]] season was the second full organised club season in Auckland following the [[1910 Auckland Rugby League season]]. It featured a representative program in August and September where [[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] went undefeated. The season commenced on the 20th of May, with the start of the competition for the Myers Cup.\n\nUnlike in 1910 when only two venues were used, there were 5 venues used. They were [[Victoria Park, Auckland|Victoria Park]], Takapuna Racecourse, 'Avondale', [[Auckland Domain]], and [[Eden Park]] (which was the venue for the club final between [[City Rovers]] and [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]].\n\n==Eden Ramblers Formed==\nThe senior competition saw the addition of the Eden Ramblers who had been formed in April. A meeting was held at the Avondale Public Hall on Wednesday 26 April with Mr [[John Bollard (politician)|John Bollard, MP]] presiding over it. He was elected president and chairman, and the name Eden Ramblers was chosen along with the colours or green and gold. The following officers were selected: Hon Secretary, Mr B Boone; Management Committee, W. A. Cummings, J Eddoes, W Fairweather, M Morrow, and J Denyer. The membership was close to 50 and they were to begin their training for the season ahead on April 29 with a join practice with Ponsonby at Victoria Park.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Eden Ramblers Club\n| page = 4\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume XLVIII, Issue 14666\n| date = 1911-04-28\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19110428.2.10\n| accessdate = 2019-12-09}}</ref>\n\n{{s-start}}\n        {{s-bef|before=[[1910 Auckland Rugby League season|1910]]}}\n        {{s-ttl|title=3rd [[Auckland Rugby League]] season\n        |years=\t1911}}\n        {{s-aft|after=[[1912 Auckland Rugby League season|1912]]}}\n        {{end}}\n\n==Myers Cup==\nEighteen regular season matches were played before the final on the 16th of September where [[City Rovers]] defeated [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]] 36 to 15 to retain the title which they had won in 1910.\n\n===Final Standings===\n{|\n|-\n|\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=175 |Team\n!width=20 abbr=\"Played\" |Pld\n!width=20 abbr=\"Won\" |W\n!width=20 abbr=\"Drawn\" |D\n!width=20 abbr=\"Lost\" |L\n!width=20 abbr=\"For\" |F\n!width=20 abbr=\"Against\" |A\n!width=20 abbr=\"Points\" |Pts\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[City Rovers]]\n|8||7||0||1||164||70||'''14'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]]\n|9||7||0||2||205||117||'''14'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[North Shore Albions]]\n|7||3||0||4||80||68||'''6'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Newton Rangers]]\n|7||1||0||6||51||138||'''2'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Eden Ramblers]]\n|7||1||0||6||42||149||'''2'''\n|-\n|}\nThe second round did not feature the final round of matches hence [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby]] playing an extra match (when they were due to have a bye), while the table also includes the final played between [[City Rovers|City]] and [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby]].\n\n==Myers Cup Fixtures and Results==\n===Round 1===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 May\n| time =\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 19-3\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Ponsonby v Newton\n| page = 8\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume XLII, Issue 120\n| date = 1911-05-22\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19110522.2.65\n| accessdate = 2019-12-09}}</ref>\n| away = Newton\n| try1 = [[Charlie Savory]], S Cole, C Dillamore, Syd Riley 2\n| con1 = S Cole 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Sainsbury\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria park\n| attendance =\n| referee = Jaggs\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 May\n| time =\n| home = City\n| score = 13-3\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =City v North Shore\n| page = 8\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume XLII, Issue 120\n| date = 1911-05-22\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19110522.2.65\n| accessdate = 2019-12-09}}</ref>\n| away = North Shore\n| try1 = William Moeki, [[Jim Rukutai]]\n| con1 = [[Alex Stanaway]] 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Haddon\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance =\n| referee = W Pitts\n}}\n\n===Round 2===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 27 May\n| time =\n| home = City\n| score = 16-3\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Newton v City\n| page = 8\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume XLII, Issue 126\n| date = 1911-05-29\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19110529.2.78.7\n| accessdate = 2019-12-09}}</ref>\n| away = Newton\n| try1 = [[Frank Morse (rugby league)|Frank Morse]] 2, [[Sid Kean]], George Harrison\n| con1 = [[Frank Morse (rugby league)|Frank Morse]]\n| pen1 = [[Albert Asher]]\n| try2 = [[Arthur Francis (rugby)|Arthur Francis]]\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Takapuna Racecourse\n| attendance =\n| referee = R Oliphant\n}}\n\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 27 May\n| time =\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 49-10\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Newton v City\n| page = 8\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume XLII, Issue 126\n| date = 1911-05-29\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt